narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: It's different every week. You'll learn about the Navy a lot.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: engaging, diverse, interactive Weaknesses: redundant for some weeks

The course is necessary if the student is interested in or is on scholarship with Yale Naval ROTC, and enables the midshipmen a separate course to learn about naval news, policy, and naval culture, and has low-to-zero amounts of outside work. The only real weaknesses to the Naval lab is the time schedule. At 1230-230, the class occupies prime scheduling space that could be used for language or STEM classes. In addition, some of the presentations, from cyberwarfare to sexual harassment prevention, while necessary, are quite dry, and more effort should be given towards breaking these up into smaller groups, for both discussion, and to enable the midshipmen to interact more with the officers.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I recommend this course if you are thinking about joining ROTC on campus, or want to gain insight into naval culture.

Yale NROTC midshipman will receive valuable instruction in various warfare communities' training pipelines and will participate in seminar-style discussions regarding command climate in the Navy. I would certainly recommend this course to other midshipmen for these reasons.
If you're in NROTC, then you'll take it. Some of the labs are pretty fun.
